frameDefinitions: A Cause leads to the formation of a Created_entity.
After a period in which the Agent has been working on a Goal, the Agent manages to attain it.
A Competition comes to an end, with a Competitor tying, winning, or losing against an Opponent (or opponents) according to their Score.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
A Cause, animate or inanimate, causes a process, the Effect, to begin.
frameExamples: Unbelievable--he <t>lost</t> the gold medal by just .02 points!
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
The murder of Sergei Kirov <t>set off</t> a chain of events that culminated in the Great Terror of the 1930s.
listRoleDefinitions: A force, process, or event that produces an effect.
Agents in a joint or reciprocal action (e.g. exchange)
A positive or negative evaluation of the Phenomenon.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.

Where the event takes place.

This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.

This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> achieves their <fen>Goal</fen>.

The location at which the <fen>Competition</fen> takes place.
